verbose_text: The airway inflammation induced by antigen exposure was significantly augmented by the intranasal administration of S1P : the cell number in BALFs of the S1P treated, antigen challenged mice (S1P Challenged, 48.9 +/-4.8 x 10 4 / mL BALF) was significantly increased as compared with those of the vehicle treated, antigen challenged ones (Vehicle Challenged, 26.3 +/-5.7 x 10 4 / mL BALF, P < 0.01).
